requirement: User should be able to log in using email and password.

structured_test_cases.test_case: TC001 - Login with Valid Email and Password
structured_test_cases.objective: To verify that user can successfully log in using a valid email and password.
preconditions: User has created an account with a valid email address.
Email is active and not suspended.
test_steps: Open the application homepage in a web browser.
Enter valid email and password in respective fields.
expected_results: User should be logged in successfully.
Dashboard or home page should be displayed.
edge_cases: User enters invalid email (format or non-existent).
User enters weak password (less than 8 characters).

structured_test_cases.test_case: TC002 - Login with Invalid Email and Password
structured_test_cases.objective: To verify that user cannot log in using an invalid email and password.
preconditions: User has created an account with a valid email address.
Email is active and not suspended.
test_steps: Open the application homepage in a web browser.
Enter invalid email and password in respective fields.
expected_results: User should not be logged in.
edge_cases: User enters email with special characters at the beginning.
User leaves both password and email fields blank.

structured_test_cases.objective: To verify that user cannot log in using an invalid password.
preconditions: User has created an account with a valid email address.
Email is active and not suspended.
test_steps: Open the application homepage in a web browser.
Enter valid email and invalid password in respective fields.
expected_results: User should not be logged in.
edge_cases: User enters password with special characters only.
User leaves email field blank but enters password.

structured_test_cases.objective: Verify user can login with correct email and password
preconditions: Email and password are correctly entered
test_steps: Enter email and password in the respective fields

steps: Enter email to receive reset link

structured_test_cases.objective: Verify user cannot login with incorrect email and/or password
test_steps: Enter email and/or password in the respective fields with incorrect values
expected_results: User is not successfully logged in, error message displayed

structured_test_cases.objective: Verify user cannot login if email is not registered
test_steps: Enter email and password in the respective fields with non-registered email
expected_results: User is not successfully logged in, error message displayed

structured_test_cases.objective: Verify user cannot login if password is incorrect
test_steps: Enter email and password in the respective fields with wrong password
expected_results: User is not successfully logged in, error message displayed

structured_test_cases.objective: Verify user cannot login if both email and password are incorrect
test_steps: Enter email and password in the respective fields with non-registered email and wrong password
expected_results: User is not successfully logged in, error message displayed

structured_test_cases.objective: Verify user can login with different cases for email and password
test_steps: Enter email and password in the respective fields with different cases

structured_test_cases.objective: Verify user cannot login if session has expired
test_steps: Open the login page after a long time since last login
Enter email and password in the respective fields with correct values
expected_results: User is not successfully logged in, error message displayed

structured_test_cases.objective: Verify user can logout and then login again with same email and password
test_steps: Enter email and password in the respective fields with correct values
Click on the login button to login successfully
Navigate to logout page and click on logout button
Try logging in again with same email and password
